AdvisorModule.Caption: Object in experiment does not run
AdvisorModule.Description: An object was created from the Toolbox in E-Studio or with E-Basic but never runs on a Procedure or through InLine script.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Volatile Clock
AdvisorModule.Description: The E-Prime Primary Clock is configured in a way that could cause timing inconsistencies. Contact PST Tech Support to configure the clock for more stabilized performance when this finding is detected.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Procedure ends with pending InputMask objects
AdvisorModule.Description: There are input masks that continue to collect responses at the end of a Procedure. To ensure that responses are collected and properly logged, set the TimeLimit property to (until feedback) or (end of proc) and the Procedure.ProcessPendingInputMasks property to All or Last.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Task Action Protracted
AdvisorModule.Description: Task Action took an excessive amount of time that can lead to timing errors

AdvisorModule.Caption: Task Action Skipped
AdvisorModule.Description: Task Action skipped because Management Mode was active when the task was scheduled

AdvisorModule.Caption: Movie and audio stimuli not mapped
AdvisorModule.Description: A movie or audio file is not using mappings available through Codec Config. Failure to map movie or audio files to specific codecs can negatively affect timing and performance of movies and sounds while running the experiment.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Duration not divisible by refresh rate
AdvisorModule.Description: An object with its OnsetSync property set to (vertical blank) has a Duration value that is not divisible by the DisplayDevice calulated refresh rate, which can lead to larger OnsetDelay and other timing issues.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Non-Visual object using OnsetSync or OffsetSync
AdvisorModule.Description: A non-visual object (SoundOut, SoundIn, Wait) has either of its OnsetSync or OffsetSync properties set to (vertical blank) which is usually unnecessary unless syncing with external equipment.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Text object has matching BackColor and ForeColor
AdvisorModule.Description: A TextDisplay or SlideText object has BackStyle set to opaque with identical values for BackColor and ForeColor, which can lead to an object not being visible during an experiment.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Use of ClearAfter
AdvisorModule.Description: An object has its ClearAfter property set to Yes. ClearAfter is a deprecated property.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Use of Stretch
AdvisorModule.Description: A visual object has its Stretch property set to Yes, which can cause display timing anomalies. Instead of using Stretch, consider editing the source material to match the size and proportions you want to display during the experiment.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Display adapter set to clone mode
AdvisorModule.Description: The display adapter of the machine is set to clone or mirror mode. Mirroring can cause timing issues since vertical blank synchronization is not accurate between multiple displays, and determining which display is considered primary can cause confusion and may not be consistent between computer configurations.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Large OnsetDelay
AdvisorModule.Description: An object is collecting OnsetDelay Stats and has an OnsetDelay that is larger than a single refresh. Setting the Duration property to a value divisible by the refresh rate and the PreRelease property to (same as duration) will typically reduce OnsetDelay values.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Use of WaitForVerticalBlank when FlippingEnabled
AdvisorModule.Description: The DisplayDevice.WaitForVerticalBlank E-Basic command is used when the DisplayDevice.FlippingEnabled property is set to Yes/True. Calling WaitForVerticalBlank while flipping is enabled can cause timing concerns.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Direct Canvas Commands
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when a Canvas command other than Copy is invoked that would directly alter the screen contents. It is recommended to perform all Canvas drawing on an offscreen Canvas and then use the Copy method to display the contents to the screen.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Value Default is not evenly divisible by Number of Decimals
AdvisorModule.Description: A SlideSlider sub-object Value Default property is not evenly divisible by the Number of Decimals property.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Interactive List was active
AdvisorModule.Description: An Interactive List was active

AdvisorModule.Caption: Evaluate SoundDevice.API
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when a SoundDevice is using the DirectSound(TM) API on Windows Vista or later which typically cannot achieve latency values under 30ms. Chronos, ASIO, or CoreAudio are recommended for Windows Vista or later. Use SoundTester to choose the most appropriate API for the experiment computer.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Major Ticks Units is not evenly divisible by Number of Decimals
AdvisorModule.Description: A SlideSlider sub-object Major Ticks Units property is not evenly divisible by the Number of Decimals property.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Successive Operation
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when Chronos.History or Chronos.AnalogIn(x).History is accessed during a time when digital or analog input data may be in transit which may lead to delayed reaction to response collection. To avoid this warning, provide enough time between Chronos.History and digital out access or Chronos.AnalogIn(x).History and analog input access

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Analog In Record with Zero Sample Rate
AdvisorModule.Description: An Analog In recording was started with the Sample Rate property set to zero.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Large Clock Offset
AdvisorModule.Description: A large clock offset LCO value was detected when sync time base between Chronos and E-Prime that can lead to timing errors

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Large Clock Flight Time
AdvisorModule.Description: A large flight time was detected when sync time base between Chronos and E-Prime that can lead to timing errors

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Clock Auto Sync Disabled
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when the auto sync of clock between Chronos and E-Prime has been disabled which can lead to timing errors

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Audio Out Buffer Underrun in MixMode1
AdvisorModule.Description: An instance of a audio data buffer underrun ocurred while in MixMode1 during a scenario that was not expected and may lead to audio data not being represented to the participant as expected

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Audio In Voicekey Pressed During Logging
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when the voiceky is pressed during the StopAfterLog processing which can lead to unexpected omission of voicekey on subsequent trials

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Audio In PostOffsetInterval too small
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when the PostOffsetInterval is assigned to a value smaller than 50ms which likely will not pickup most human speech patterns

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Audio In File Exists
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when an Audio In recording is overwriting a file which could lead to missed data

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Analog Out Waveform Clipped
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when generating or loading an analog waveform has values clipped larger than 100% or smaller than 0%

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Analog Out playback with zero loop position
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when an Analog Out playback begins with a PlaybackRate value of zero

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Analog In Threshold Adjustment
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when adjustment to the OnsetThreshold or OffsetThreshold require adjustments to both thresholds

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Analog In StreamPumpInterval zero
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when the Chronos Analog In StreamPumpInterval has been set to zero which can have a negative effect on machine performance and analog data collection

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Analog In ScaledMin greater than ScaledMax
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when the ScaledMin value is greater than the ScaledMax value for an Analog In channel that can lead to unexpected sample values

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Analog In First File Overwrite
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when the first instance of an Analog In recording overwrites a file which is not expected and may indicate reuse of session data on a subsequent run

AdvisorModule.Caption: Chronos Analog In Excessive Definition
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when the definition for row and column headings is large which can lead to poor analog in sample collection

AdvisorModule.Caption: Operating System not verified
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects if the operating system used to run the experiment has not been verified by PST. When a new edition of an Operating System, patch, or service pack is released after E-Prime, there is a possibility the timing and compatibility characteristics have changed. Check www.pstnet.com for more info regarding this operating system and its usage characteristics with E-Prime.
